North Korea declared on February 10 it possessed nuclear weapons and said it needed them as a deterrent to what it said were US plans to launch a nuclear attack against it. North Korea on Monday proposed resuming six-nation talks on its nuclear program during the week of September 12, a foreign ministry spokesman was quoted by the North's official KCNA news agency as saying. But the road ahead -- with North Korea and with Iran, which has rejected a European proposal to curb its nuclear program in return for generous benefits -- looks bumpy at best. 